HEADWORD: Prolonge
<hw>Pro*longe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Prolong</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Field Artillery)</fld> <def>A rope with a
hook and a toggle, sometimes used to drag a gun carriage or to lash it
to the limber, and for various other purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolonger</ent>⟦br⟧
